This paper deals with power assignment in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and graph theory. Specifically, the paper focuses on the dual power assignment problem, which involves assigning high- or low-power levels to wireless nodes to ensure a strongly connected induced graph with minimum cost. This problem is relevant to the sub-category of computer networks (cs.NI) and graph theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper utilizes interesting properties related to the existence of a second Hamiltonian cycle, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm with improved approximation ratio, which is a topic related to algorithm design and analysis (cs.SI).
